Acme T-Shirt Company charges a $\$50$ set-up fee plus $\$9$ for  each shirt printed. Beta T-shirt Company has no set up fee, but charges $\$14$ per shirt. What is the minimum number of shirts for which a customer saves money by using Acme?
inference:
Let $x$ be the number of shirts.
Acme T-shirt Company charges a $\$50$ set-up fee plus $\$9$ for each shirt printed.
The cost for Acme is $50 + 9x$.
Beta T-shirt Company has no set-up fee, but charges $\$14$ per shirt.
The cost for Beta is $14x$.
We want to find the minimum number of shirts for which a customer saves money by using Acme.
This means we want to find the minimum $x$ such that the cost for Acme is less than the cost for Beta.
$50 + 9x < 14x$
$50 < 14x - 9x$
$50 < 5x$
$x > \frac{50}{5}$
$x > 10$
Thus, the minimum number of shirts for which a customer saves money by using Acme is 11.
Final Answer: $\boxed{11}$ I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
We want to find the lowest integer $x$ such that: \begin{align*}
50+9x&<14x \quad \Rightarrow \\
50&<5x \quad \Rightarrow \\
10&<x.
\end{align*}The least integer greater than 10 is $\boxed{11}$.
